signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Kickers with this ability experience a slower kicking meter for better power and accuracy on kicks over 45 yards.
Kickers with this ability experience a slower kicking meter for better power and accuracy on kicks up to 45 yards.
Kickers with this ability can see the entirety of the kicking arc
Players with this ability are harder to knock out of The Zone
Ballcarriers with this ability have an increased chance to break hit-stick tackle attempts made on them.
The best physical receivers don't just come down with the ball, they carry it home. When they enter the zone, they are nearly guaranteed to break their first post-catch tackle.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes 10-20 yards from the LoS, outside the numbers
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS, outside the numbers
When lined up in the slot, receivers with this ability make faster cuts and have better hands when catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS
After securing a RAC catch, ballcarriers with this ability can quickly shift momentum, change direction, and turn the corner without sacrificing speed.
Defenders with this ability use faster, more dominant pass rush moves while rushing from the edge of the defense.
Defenders with this ability will frequently attempt and win impact blocks against receivers, tight ends, and running backs.
Defenders with this ability have an increased success rate when using conservative or diving tackles.
While in the pocket, passers with this ability are almost guaranteed to break the first sack attempt by a blitzing defensive back.
Passers with this ability have a reduced chance to be impacted by throw penalties caused by defensive pressure while on the run
Vanguard players are the reason running backs thank their blockers in the postgame interview. When they enter the zone, they are nearly guaranteed dominant impact block wins.
